# Walkthrough: Brand Palette and Layout Enhancements

I've successfully implemented the brand palette enhancements, layout modifications, and the logo component updates as requested.

## Summary of Changes

### 1. Brand Palette & [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css)
- **Color Themes**: Added 7 brand new CSS color themes (`.theme-green`, `.theme-blue`, `.theme-yellow`, `.theme-fucsia`, `.theme-violet`, `.theme-red`, `.theme-orange`) based on the updated design system. Each theme uses refined primary and secondary HSL values for sharp contrast.
- **Base Backgrounds**: Optimized `--background` and `--card` colors in both light (`0 0% 100%`) and dark (`240 10% 4%`) modes for a cleaner canvas look.
- **Smooth Transitions**: Added `transition: background-color 0.3s ease, color 0.3s ease;` to `body` and `*` elements for a more premium feeling during theme toggling.
- **Public Layout Grid**: Integrated the dotted grid background pattern to `.layout-public-root` (`radial-gradient` overlay with `24px` spacing).

### 2. Logo Components Updates
- **Dynamic Icons**: Both [Logo](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/admin/app/components/ui/Logo.tsx#35-102) components (Public & Admin) now accept `color` and `bg` props to seamlessly switch between the full textual logo and the new square icon variations.
- **Background Logic**: Depending on the `bg` prop, the correct colored or monochrome icon is loaded into an appropriately sized and padded square container.
- **Clickable Links**: The Logo component content is now wrapped in a `next/link` component to act as a navigational shortcut back to the homepage (`/`).

### 3. Public Layout & Header Adjustments
- **Transparent Header**: Modified `.layout-header-main` in [globals.css](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/app/globals.css) to be fully visible and `bg-transparent`.
- **Removed Footer**: Detached `<PublicFooter />` from the public layout structure so the grid and content take up the full emphasis.

### 4. Theme and Color Selector Implementations
- **`next-themes` Verification**: Confirmed `next-themes` is actively tracking Light/Dark state in LocalStorage (in sync with `<SwitchTheme />`).
- **New [useBrandColor](file:///Users/cristiankalexai/Progetti/standlo.com/src/hooks/useBrandColor.ts#9-44) Hook**: Authored a streamlined custom hook that automatically manages string states (e.g. `"green"`, `"red"`) with `localStorage` persistence, dynamically appending/removing the valid `.theme-<color>` classes on the root HTML element.
- **New `<SwitchColor />` Component**: Formatted to match the existing `<SwitchTheme />` trigger, it provides a dropdown populated with all 7 colors. You can find this right alongside the theme toggle in the public header.

You should now be able to start the development server (`npm run dev`), view the public page, select any of the 7 themes alongside toggling light/dark mode, and see changes directly persist and dynamically apply to the background and primary colors!
